The paper deals with the problem of approximate nearest neighbor search in high dimensional Euclidean space, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and machine learning. The use of random projections and data structures such as BBD-trees and $r$-nets suggests that the paper belongs to the categories of data structures (cs.DS), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
